<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ISO-8859-1" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE MAN SYSTEM "../../manrev.dtd">
<MAN>
  <LANGUAGE>eng</LANGUAGE>
  <TITLE>median</TITLE>
  <TYPE>Scilab Function</TYPE>
  <DATE>April 1993</DATE>
  <SHORT_DESCRIPTION name="median"> median (row median, column median) of vector/matrix entries</SHORT_DESCRIPTION>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE>
    <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>y=median(x)  </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
    <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>y=median(x,'r')  </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
    <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>y=median(x,'c')  </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
  </CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <PARAM>
    <PARAM_INDENT>
      <PARAM_ITEM>
        <PARAM_NAME>x</PARAM_NAME>
        <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
          <SP>: real vector or matrix</SP>
        </PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
      </PARAM_ITEM>
      <PARAM_ITEM>
        <PARAM_NAME>y</PARAM_NAME>
        <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
          <SP>: scalar or vector</SP>
        </PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
      </PARAM_ITEM>
    </PARAM_INDENT>
  </PARAM>
  <DESCRIPTION>
    <P>
    For a vector or a matrix <VERB>x</VERB>, <VERB>y=median(x)</VERB>  returns in the
    scalar <VERB>y</VERB> the median of all the entries of <VERB>x</VERB>.</P>
    <P><VERB>y=median(x,'r')</VERB> (or, equivalently, <VERB>y=median(x,1)</VERB>) is the rowwise median. It returns in each 
    entry of the column vector <VERB>y</VERB> the median of each row of <VERB>x</VERB>.</P>
    <P><VERB>y=median(x,'c')</VERB> (or, equivalently, <VERB>y=median(x,2)</VERB>) is the columnwise median. It returns in each entry of the row vector 
    <VERB>y</VERB> the median of each column  of <VERB>x</VERB>.</P>
  </DESCRIPTION>
  <EXAMPLE>
<![CDATA[
A=[1,2,10;7,7.1,7.01];
median(A)
median(A,'r')
median(A,'c')
 ]]>
  </EXAMPLE>
